---
layout: base.njk
pageTitle: "CCSU LLB Previous Year Papers 2016-2025 | AI Exam Prep | Last Minute Law"
pageDescription: "AI-analyzed CCSU LLB previous year question papers (2016-2025). Smart predictions, scoring strategies, syllabus, case laws & exam tips for all 6 semesters."
---

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow fade-in"><span class="dot"></span><span>Live · 2025–2026 Exam Window</span></div>
    <h1 id="hero-heading" class="hero-title fade-in d1">Know <em>exactly</em><br>what to study.</h1>
    <p class="hero-lede fade-in d2">Every CCSU LLB question paper from 2016 to 2025, analysed. Smart predictions, proven scoring strategies, and landmark case laws — indexed for your next exam.</p>

    <div class="hero-split">
      <div class="fade-in d3">
        <div class="sem-label"><span>Browse by Semester</span><span class="sem-label-hint">Tap to switch</span></div>
        <div class="sem-row" role="tablist" aria-label="Semester selector">
          {%- for i in [1,2,3,4,5,6] %}
          <a href="{% if i == 4 %}#subjects{% else %}#{% endif %}" class="sem-btn {% if i == 4 %}active{% endif %}" role="tab">
            {% if i == 4 %}<span class="sem-btn-live">Live</span>{% endif %}
            <span class="sem-btn-num">{{ ['I','II','III','IV','V','VI'][i-1] }}</span>
            <span class="sem-btn-sub">Sem {{ i }}</span>
          </a>
          {%- endfor %}
        </div>
        <p class="sem-note">Semester IV is fully analysed. Other semesters unlock before their exam windows.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-stats fade-in d3">
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-val">45+</div>
          <div class="hero-stat-lbl">Papers Analysed</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-val">7</div>
          <div class="hero-stat-lbl">Subjects Covered</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-val">10</div>
          <div class="hero-stat-lbl">Years of Data</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <div class="hero-stat-val">100%</div>
          <div class="hero-stat-lbl">Free Forever</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SUBJECTS -->
<section id="subjects" aria-labelledby="subjects-heading">
  <header class="section-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="section-kicker">Question Bank</div>
          <h2 id="subjects-heading" class="section-title">The Papers, Decoded.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="section-deck">AI-ranked topics by appearance frequency. Every question tagged, every strategy annotated.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="subject-grid">
      {%- set subjectKeys = subjects | dictsort %}
      {%- for slug, s in subjectKeys %}
      {%- set isAvailable = s.priorities.length > 0 and s.years.length > 0 %}
      {% if isAvailable %}
      <a href="/{{ slug }}/" class="subject-card">
        <div class="sc-top"><span class="sc-num">{{ loop.index | padStart(2, '0') }}</span><span class="sc-code">{{ s.code }}</span></div>
        <h3 class="sc-name">{{ s.name }}</h3>
        <p class="sc-deck">{{ s.oneLiner }}</p>
        <div class="sc-meta">
          <span class="chip {% if s.difficulty == 'Easy' %}chip--green{% elif s.difficulty == 'Hard' %}chip--red{% else %}chip--amber{% endif %}">{{ s.difficulty or 'Medium' }}</span>
          <span class="chip chip--plain">{{ s.style }}</span>
          {%- if s.optional %}<span class="chip chip--navy">Optional</span>{%- endif %}
          {%- if s.practical %}<span class="chip">Theory + Practical</span>{%- endif %}
        </div>
        {%- if s.years.length > 0 %}
        <div class="sc-years">{%- for y in s.years %}<span class="sc-year">{{ y }}</span>{%- endfor %}</div>
        {%- endif %}
        <div class="sc-footer"><span>{{ s.papersCount }} papers</span><span class="sc-footer-right">Read <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></span></div>
      </a>
      {% else %}
      <div class="subject-card locked" aria-disabled="true">
        <span class="lock-ribbon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" width="10" height="10"><rect x="5" y="11" width="14" height="10" rx="1"/><path d="M8 11V8a4 4 0 018 0v3"/></svg>
          Coming Soon
        </span>
        <div class="sc-top"><span class="sc-num">{{ loop.index | padStart(2, '0') }}</span></div>
        <h3 class="sc-name">{{ s.name }}</h3>
        {%- if s.oneLiner %}<p class="sc-deck">{{ s.oneLiner }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <div class="sc-meta">
          {%- if s.difficulty %}<span class="chip {% if s.difficulty == 'Easy' %}chip--green{% elif s.difficulty == 'Hard' %}chip--red{% else %}chip--amber{% endif %}">{{ s.difficulty }}</span>{%- endif %}
          {%- if s.optional %}<span class="chip chip--navy">Optional</span>{%- endif %}
        </div>
        <div class="sc-footer"><span></span><span class="sc-footer-right">Coming Soon</span></div>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TIPS -->
<section id="tips" aria-labelledby="tips-heading">
  <header class="section-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="section-kicker">The Method</div>
          <h2 id="tips-heading" class="section-title">Tips &amp; Guidelines</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="section-deck">Battle-tested strategies, based on how CCSU actually checks papers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="tips-grid">

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">01</span><span class="tip-title">How CCSU Checking Actually Works</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <p><strong>Mass Evaluation Camps:</strong> Evaluators check hundreds of copies daily. They scan for visual anchors, not nuanced arguments.</p>
        <p><strong>First 3 Lines are Critical:</strong> A clean definition + Section number = paper categorised as "competent", rest skimmed favourably.</p>
        <p><strong>Visual Relief:</strong> Underlined headings, boxed case names, structured points subtly boost marks.</p>
        <p><strong>The 60% Ceiling:</strong> Most cluster at 50–60%. Above 65% requires polished presentation + accurate sections + relevant cases.</p>
      </div></details>

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">02</span><span class="tip-title">Section A Strategy · 4-mark</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <p><strong>The Hit &amp; Run:</strong> 75 words max. 3–5 minutes per question. Never overwrite — it bleeds time from Section C.</p>
        <p><strong>Formula:</strong> Direct Definition → Statutory Provision → One Case Name.</p>
        <p><strong>Time:</strong> 5 questions × 5 min = 25 minutes total.</p>
      </div></details>

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">03</span><span class="tip-title">Section B Strategy · 10-mark</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <p><strong>The Bridge:</strong> ~200 words (1.5–2 pages). 15 minutes per question.</p>
        <p><strong>Structure:</strong> Introduction → Essentials (numbered) → 1–2 Cases → Brief Conclusion.</p>
        <p>Use underlined sub-headings so the evaluator doesn't have to search for your points.</p>
      </div></details>

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">04</span><span class="tip-title">Section C Strategy · 20-mark</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <p><strong>The Endurance Test:</strong> 3–5 pages. 30 minutes per question. This section dictates your percentage.</p>
        <p><strong>Template:</strong> Intro → Definition + Section → Jurists → Elements → Cases → Exceptions → Conclusion.</p>
        <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Underline headings, box case names, leave margins. Visual formatting is proven to boost marks at CCSU.</p>
      </div></details>

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">05</span><span class="tip-title">The Scoring Sweet Spot</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <p style="color:var(--red);font-style:italic;">Moderate Quality + Good Length + Strong Structure = Highest Marks.</p>
        <p>In CCSU's ecosystem, <strong>Volume + Structure = Quality</strong>. The evaluator subconsciously equates physical length with effort.</p>
        <p><strong>Real data:</strong> A student with 3 hours of prep but 21 pages (proper headings) scored highest in Administrative Law (65/100) — beating students who prepared for days but wrote condensed answers.</p>
      </div></details>

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">06</span><span class="tip-title">Case Law Strategy · The 2-Case Rule</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <p>You do <em>not</em> need 20 cases per answer. Pick <strong>2 landmark cases</strong> for every major topic.</p>
        <p><strong>How to present:</strong> Write case names in italics or underlined → State: Name → Year → Court → One-line ratio.</p>
        <p>For scoring subjects like IPC/BNS or Family Law, accurate <strong>Section numbers</strong> break past the 60% ceiling.</p>
      </div></details>

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">07</span><span class="tip-title">Last-Day Strategy</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <p>On the final day, abandon the textbook. Focus exclusively on:</p>
        <p><strong>1. Evergreen Topics</strong> — Appear in 80%+ of papers. Guaranteed to show up.</p>
        <p><strong>2. Hot Streak Topics</strong> — Appeared in last 2–3 consecutive years. Tend to continue.</p>
        <p><strong>3. Safe Section C Combos</strong> — Pick 2 pre-prepared combos of 3 topics each.</p>
      </div></details>

      <details class="tip-item"><summary class="tip-summary">
        <div class="tip-head"><span class="tip-kicker">08</span><span class="tip-title">The 3-Hour Time Plan</span></div>
        <span class="tip-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
      </summary>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <table class="rule-table" style="margin:4px 0;">
          <tr><td>Read paper + plan</td><td>10 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Section A (5 × 4)</td><td>25 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Section B (2 × 10)</td><td>30 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Section C (3 × 20)</td><td>90 min</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Review + finishing</td><td>15 min</td></tr>
          <tr class="total"><td>Total</td><td>170 min</td></tr>
        </table>
        <p style="font-size:11px;color:var(--ink-60);">Always start with Sec A (quick wins), then Sec C (max marks), then Sec B.</p>
      </div></details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRIVIA -->
<section style="padding: 60px 0;">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="trivia">
      <div class="trivia-kicker">Did You Know?</div>
      <p class="trivia-text" id="triviaText">India's Constitution is the longest written constitution in the world, with 395 Articles (originally) and 12 Schedules.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <header class="section-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head-inner">
        <div>
          <div class="section-kicker">Common Questions</div>
          <h2 id="faq-heading" class="section-title">FAQ</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="faq-grid">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><span class="faq-q">What is the passing mark for CCSU LLB?</span><span class="faq-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span></summary>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p><strong>36 out of 100 (36%)</strong> per paper is required to pass each CCSU LLB subject.</p>
          <p>Total 500 marks per semester across 5 papers. For practical papers (K-3005, K-4007, K-5005, K-6008), you must pass both the theory (50 marks) and practical (50 marks) components independently.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><span class="faq-q">What is the CCSU LLB exam pattern?</span><span class="faq-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span></summary>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>Each 3-hour paper has <strong>100 marks</strong> split into three sections:</p>
          <p><strong>Section A:</strong> 5 compulsory questions × 4 marks = 20 marks</p>
          <p><strong>Section B:</strong> 2 of 3 questions × 10 marks = 20 marks</p>
          <p><strong>Section C:</strong> 3 of 5 questions × 20 marks = 60 marks</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><span class="faq-q">Can I fail papers and still pass the semester?</span><span class="faq-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span></summary>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p><strong>Yes — if you fail 1 or 2 papers</strong>, you are promoted to the next semester and must clear them as back papers.</p>
          <p><strong>Failing 3 or more papers</strong> results in semester back — you must repeat the entire semester.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary><span class="faq-q">Which optional subject should I choose in Semester IV?</span><span class="faq-chev"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span></summary>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p><strong>Banking Law (K-4006)</strong> is most commonly offered and easiest for definition-based scoring — NI types, RBI functions, cheque dishonour.</p>
          <p><strong>Criminology (K-4004)</strong> is best for essay writers. <strong>Law of Trust (K-4005)</strong> is rarely offered by colleges.</p>
          <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--ink-40);font-style:italic;">Tip: Check which optionals your college actually offers before deciding.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

